{"type":"message","id":"cd272c37","parentId":"603c61d5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:29:23.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, Claude Code might be installed in a different location, or it might not be installed at all on the Windows side. The issue is that even though I can see the Windows filesystem through /mnt/c, I'm still running the Linux version of Claude Code (or any commands I run are executed in the Linux environment).\n\nActually, there's a fundamental issue here: even if I find the Windows executable, I can't directly run a Windows .exe from WSL2 Linux. WSL can run some Windows executables, but it's limited and may have issues.\n\nThe real solution would be:\n1. Have Claude Code installed and logged in on the Linux side (WSL2)\n2. Or use a different approach to access the Windows Claude Code\n\nLet me explain this to the user.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找不到 Windows 里的 Claude Code。而且就算能找到，WSL2 环境也很难直接运行 Windows 的 .exe 文件。\n\n**可行的解决方案：**\n\n1. **在 WSL2 里也装一个 Claude Code**（推荐）\n   ```bash\n   npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n   claude /login\n   ```\n\n2. **或者我在当前环境用 Codex**（功能类似，也支持代码任务）\n\n你想怎么处理？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":51609,"output":252,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775233759784,"responseId":"chatcmpl-480d711c-4e3f-4c6f-8de0-6d648a53e1a0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"672c89ac","parentId":"cd272c37","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:32:13.376Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-04 00:31:52 GMT+8] Exec failed (crisp-re, signal SIGTERM) :: /mnt/c/Users/ll/AppData/Local/Microsoft/WinGet/Packages/Anthropic.ClaudeCode_Microsoft.Winget.Source_8wekyb3d8bbwe/claude.exe /mnt/c/Users/ll/AppData/Local/Temp/WinGet/Anthropic.C…\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b53caf672b8a0c11a5f3f1f6c2b6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 00:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b53caf672b8a0c11a5f3f1f6c2b6]\nou_f078a2787ee791cfa7b974fd499fd49f: 尝试一下：解决方案：用环境变量为 WSL 里的 Claude Code 指条“明路”\n与其让它去一个空文件夹里找，不如我们直接通过环境变量告诉它该去哪里找。既然你已经有了 API Key（比如来自 Coding Plan 的），我们可以用 ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN 这个环境变量来为 WSL 里的 Claude Code 提供认证。\n\n步骤 1：为 OpenClaw 配置 Claude Code 环境变量\nOpenClaw 在调用 claude 命令时，会继承它自己的服务环境。我们需要找到正确的地方来设置这个变量。\n\n打开 OpenClaw 的服务环境文件：\n\nbash\n# 编辑 OpenClaw 网关的环境文件，如果不存在则创建\nsudo nano /etc/default/openclaw\n(如果你不确定 OpenClaw 安装的具体情况，也可以尝试将环境变量写入 ~/.openclaw/.env 文件中。nano 是一个简单易用的命令行文本编辑器，编辑完后按 Ctrl+X，再按 Y 确认保存即可。)\n\n在文件中添加 API Key：\n在文件里写入以下内容，将 <你的API_Key> 替换为你真实有效的 Key。\n\nbash\nANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=<你的API_Key>\n(如果你用的是兼容 OpenAI 格式的 API 代理，通常还需要额外指定 ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL 和 ANTHROPIC_MODEL，具体可以咨询你的 API 服务提供商)\n\n重启 OpenClaw 服务：\n保存文件后，重启 OpenClaw 的网关服务让变量生效。\n\nbash\nsudo systemctl restart openclaw-gateway\n步骤 2：验证配置\n配置完成后，你需要确认它是否生效了。\n\n检查环境变量：你可以运行 sudo systemctl show openclaw-gateway --property=Environment 来检查环境变量是否已正确加载。\n\n测试 Claude Code：在 WSL 终端里直接输入 claude，如果能正常启动或返回信息，说明认证已成功。\n\n进行健康检查：最后，在 OpenClaw 中运行 openclaw doctor 进行全面检查。如果看到类似 OpenClaw is healthy 的字样，就说明所有配置都正确无误了。"}],"timestamp":1775233933371}}
